\[\begin{align*}
	\ln(x+6)+\ln(2-x) &amp;= \ln 15 \\
	\ln[(x+6)(2-x)] &amp;= \ln{15} \\
	\ln(-x^2-4x+12) &amp;= \ln{15} \\
	e^{\ln(-x^2-4x+12)} &amp;= e^{\ln{15}} \\
	-x^2-4x+12 &amp;= 15 \\
	x^2+4x+3 &amp;= 0
\end{align*}\]

<p>Then factor the equation,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	(x+3)(x+1) &amp;= 0
\end{align*}\]

<p>Thus,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	x+3 &amp;= 0    &amp;   x+1 &amp;= 0 \\
	x &amp;= -3 &amp;   x &amp;= -1     \tagans
\end{align*}\]

